SIMPLE: malpighian
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Malpighian
<hw>Mal*pi"ghi*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>
<def>Of, pertaining to, or discovered by, <person>Marcello
<etsep>Malpighi</etsep></person>, an Italian anatomist of the 17th
century.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><mcol><col><b>Malpighian capsules</b></col> <it>or</it>
<col><b>Malpighian corpuscles</b></col></mcol> <fld>(Anatomy)</fld>,
<cd>the globular dilatations, containing the glomeruli or Malpighian
tufts, at the extremities of the urinary tubules of the kidney.</cd> --
<col><b>Malpighian corpuscles of the spleen</b></col>, <cd>masses of
adenoid tissue connected with branches of the splenic
artery.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>malpighian body</ent>⟦br⟧
